1. Email Spam Detection
Objective

Build a model that can classify emails as Spam or Not Spam (Ham).

Dataset

Spam email dataset containing labeled messages:

Spam

Ham (not spam)

Steps Performed

Data Loading

Text Cleaning and Preprocessing

Feature Engineering using TF-IDF

Model Training

Model Evaluation

Prediction Testing

Models Used

Naive Bayes

Logistic Regression

Support Vector Machine (SVM)

Feature Engineering

TF-IDF (Term Frequency – Inverse Document Frequency) was used to convert text into numerical vectors.

Example pipeline:

Text → Cleaning → TF-IDF → Model → Prediction

Evaluation Metrics

Accuracy

Confusion Matrix

Precision

Recall

F1 Score

Results

Machine learning models such as Naive Bayes and Logistic Regression performed very well, achieving high accuracy for spam classification.

2. Movie Sentiment Analysis
Objective

Classify movie reviews into:

Positive

Negative

This project compares Deep Learning vs Machine Learning approaches for text classification.

Dataset

Movie review dataset containing labeled sentiments.

Data Processing

Steps used in preprocessing:

Lowercasing

Removing punctuation

Removing stopwords

Tokenization

Text vectorization

Feature Engineering

Two approaches were tested:

TF-IDF

Word embeddings

Models Implemented

Machine Learning Models

Naive Bayes

Logistic Regression

Support Vector Machine

Deep Learning Model

LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)

Observations

Machine learning models using TF-IDF performed very well on smaller datasets.
Deep learning models required more data and careful regularization to avoid overfitting.

Evaluation

Models were evaluated using:

Accuracy

Validation accuracy

Loss curves

Confusion matrix

3. Text Classification Experiments

This section includes experiments with different text classification techniques.

Topics explored include:

Feature engineering for text

TF-IDF vectorization

Word embeddings

Model comparison

Models explored:

Naive Bayes

Logistic Regression

Support Vector Machines

Key goal:

Understanding how different models perform on text classification tasks.

4. CNN Image Classification (Dogs vs Cats)
Objective

Build a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to classify images as:

Dog

Cat

Dataset

Dogs vs Cats image dataset.

Image Preprocessing

Steps included:

Image resizing

Normalization

Data splitting (training / validation)

CNN Architecture

The CNN model includes:

Convolution layers

ReLU activation

MaxPooling layers

Fully connected layers

Dropout for regularization

Training

The model was trained using:

Binary cross entropy loss

Adam optimizer

Evaluation

Model performance was evaluated using:

Training accuracy

Validation accuracy

Loss curves

Technologies Used

Python
NumPy
Pandas
Scikit-learn
TensorFlow / Keras
Matplotlib
Seaborn
NLTK

Key Learnings

Through these projects, the following concepts were explored:

Text preprocessing for NLP

Feature engineering using TF-IDF

Comparison of Machine Learning vs Deep Learning models

Overfitting and regularization techniques

CNN architecture for image classification

Model evaluation and performance analysis

